spans.text: Poets their own Verses Sung , A Verse
rear them to a goodly Pile
rear them to a goodly Pile
one of all our tuneful Throng
On Earth , the God of Wealth
On Earth , the God of Wealth
On Earth , the God of Wealth
their old Pretence To lodge in Garrats
The better Half we had to say
Sing Muse the House of Poet V— In higher Strains
) Is both a Herald and a Poet , No
Repair a House gone to Decay
Fit to Invade or prop the Skies
to Invade or prop the Skies
Told V— he knew his Talent best
a French Play as lawful Prise
a French Play as lawful Prise
a French Play as lawful Prise
( like a Wag ) sat down to Write , Would whisper to himself
Build Babel with their Tongues confounded
Build Babel with their Tongues confounded
it best To turn the Matter to a Jest
the God , are these your Tricks
a Wall So wide as to encompass all
no more Than a few Scrubby Trees before
no more Than a few Scrubby Trees before
deep , and so A Cellar next
a shift To raise a Roof with Act the Fift
A Place not decent here to name
all Quarters ran To see the House of Brother V—
ran To see the House of Brother V—
asks the Watermen hard by , Where may the Poets Place lie
the Watermen hard by , Where may the Poets Place lie
they in the Rubbish spy A Thing resembling a Goose
For every Wit in Britain's Isle
a Power From the dead Ashes of a Flower Some faint Resemblance to produce , But not the Virtue , Taste or Juice
From the dead Ashes of a Flower
The Poetry of Ages past , Which after they have overthrown
